The kinetics of cell growth, hydrogen production, acetic acid production, and consumption of E. harbinese B49 and R. faecalis RLD-53 were investigated under their own optimal conditions [26,27] with a logistic model, modified Gompertz equation, and modified Richards model, respectively (Figure 1), and the main kinetic parameters are summarized in Table 1. At a glucose concentration of 10 g/L, the maximum hydrogen production rate (RH2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
